  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-2447].
  {panel}

I like the hot referers but I only want humans to see them, not robots.  Occasionally I link into Confluence from some secret development page and then it's logged in the hot referer section.  Then Google gets a hold of it and now my secret development URL is not so secret.

Why not have the "Hot Referrers" navigation block only show up in authenticated sessions?  I know I can do this by editing the Velocity and making a theme, but I think it's sensible enough that it be the default.

Cheers.

